## 🔥 Fix #1 — `vite.config.ts` — Biggest Impact

**Problem:** Zero build optimization. No code splitting, no compression, no minification config. This alone accounts for **~3,800 KiB** of savings (text compression + unused JS + minification).

```ts
// vite.config.ts — BEFORE
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import react from "@vitejs/plugin-react";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
});
```

```ts
// vite.config.ts — AFTER
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import react from "@vitejs/plugin-react";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  build: {
    minify: "terser",
    terserOptions: {
      compress: { drop_console: true },
    },
    rollupOptions: {
      output: {
        manualChunks: {
          vendor: ["react", "react-dom"],
          redux: ["@reduxjs/toolkit", "react-redux"],
          router: ["react-router-dom"],
          styled: ["styled-components"],
        },
      },
    },
  },
});
```

Also install and add gzip/brotli compression (handles the **2,576 KiB** text compression opportunity):

```bash
npm install -D vite-plugin-compression
```

```ts
